# Implementation Plan

**Spec**: speckit.specify
**Generated**: 2026-05-11

## Summary

Build a web-based subtitle editing tool (Prism Timeline) that loads video + SRT, provides a video-editor-style timeline for drag/move/resize of subtitle segments, supports text/timing editing, keyboard shortcuts, zoom/scroll, and exports back to SRT.

## Technical Context

- **Language/Version**: TypeScript 5.x
- **Runtime**: Browser (web app)
- **Framework**: React 18 + Vite
- **State Management**: Zustand
- **Timeline**: Custom Canvas-based rendering
- **Testing**: Vitest (unit) + Playwright (e2e)
- **Target Platform**: Modern browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Edge)

## Constitution Check

- ✅ Timeline precision first: millisecond-level timing in engine, integer ms throughout
- ✅ Non-destructive editing: Zustand + undo middleware for full undo/redo
- ✅ Fast iterative workflow: keyboard-first, real-time preview
- ✅ Interoperable I/O: strict SRT parser, standards-compliant export
- ✅ Cross-platform: web-first, no native dependencies
- ✅ Observable quality: parser + engine + round-trip tests

